Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Pour the @water{100%ml} into a large #saucepan{} over high heat. Add the @BBQ sauce{64%g} and the @white wine vinegar{12%ml}. Add a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} to the pan, bring the mixture to the boil and stir to combine.

Once the liquid is boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low, add the @chicken thigh{260%g}(diced) and stir into the sauce. Cover the pan with a #lid{}. Simmer until the chicken is cooked, ~{15-20%minutes}. Stir halfway through cooking.

> TIP: Reduce the heat if the sauce is bubbling too rapidly. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat and transfer the chicken to a #plate{} or #chopping board{}.

Meanwhile, chop the @baking potato{1} into 1cm wide slices, then chop the slices into 1cm wide chips. Pop them on a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat evenly, spread in a single layer on the tray and roast on the top shelf of your oven until browned and crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Zest and halve the @lime{1}. Trim, then coarsely grate the @carrot{1}. Roughly chop the @coriander{1} (stalks and all). Drain and rinse the @black beans{1} in a #sieve{}, put half of them in a #bowl{}. Mash the black beans in the bowl until nicely broken up using a #potato masher{}. Grate the @half-fat mature cheddar cheese{30%g}. Once the chicken is out of the sauce, use two #forks{} to shred the chicken as finely as you can. Meanwhile, return the pan to high heat and rapidly boil the sauce until reduced by half, ~{4-5%minutes}.

When the sauce has reduced, remove from the heat. Add the pulled chicken back into the pan along with the black beans (both whole and mashed). Add the cheddar cheese, lime zest and half the coriander, stir together. Divide the chicken mixture between the middle of each @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} (two per person). Roll up the tortillas, place them snugly in a lightly oiled #ovenproof dish{} seam-side down. Drizzle them with a little oil.

Move the chips to the middle shelf of your oven and bake the enchiladas on the top shelf until golden, ~{10-15%minutes}. Meanwhile, squeeze the lime juice into a bowl and add the @olive oil{1%tbsp} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Mix together then stir in the carrot and remaining coriander. Once everything is ready, serve the enchiladas with the chips and the carrot slaw on the side. Enjoy!